01:12:17,374 --> 01:12:19,501
Does he survive the crash?

501
01:12:20,586 --> 01:12:22,963
Big drama the next few hours.

502
01:12:23,714 --> 01:12:28,093
But whatever happens, no 
matter what they tell you,

503
01:12:29,887 --> 01:12:31,889
don't let 'em take 
these chains off me.

504
01:12:32,848 --> 01:12:34,808
Them? Who's "them"? Who 
are you talking...

505
01:12:34,892 --> 01:12:36,894
Do you know who you're 
talking to here?

506
01:12:41,357 --> 01:12:42,608
That was for me?

507
01:12:46,028 --> 01:12:48,113
For the historical record,

508
01:12:49,907 --> 01:12:51,033
he made it.

509
01:12:57,414 --> 01:12:59,166
So it's just you and him?

510
01:13:00,375 --> 01:13:01,585
Was, uh,

511
01:13:02,795 --> 01:13:05,547
about the same number you 
see here in this room.

512
01:13:07,174 --> 01:13:09,176
So how many made it off?

513
01:13:09,885 --> 01:13:11,095
Three.

514
01:13:12,638 --> 01:13:13,972
But not him?

515
01:13:15,933 --> 01:13:17,142
No.

516
01:13:17,810 --> 01:13:20,145
So between the time of the crash and 
the time you leave that planet,

517
01:13:21,146 --> 01:13:23,565
my son dies.

518
01:13:23,982 --> 01:13:28,487
And I can safely assume it's 
at your hands. Is that right?

519
01:13:31,406 --> 01:13:32,199
Tell me what you see 
outside that window, Dahl.

520
01:13:32,991 --> 01:13:37,621
Tell me what you see 
outside that window, Dahl.

521
01:13:48,757 --> 01:13:50,968
Cyclops unit, two ships,

522
01:13:51,343 --> 01:13:53,595
couple dead guys in plastic.

523
01:13:54,263 --> 01:13:56,014
And you don't see anything else?

524
01:13:56,181 --> 01:13:57,683
Nothing else.

525
01:14:15,701 --> 01:14:17,077
Time's up.

526
01:14:23,459 --> 01:14:24,835
Time is up.

527
01:14:26,628 --> 01:14:28,380
He's all yours.

528
01:14:35,304 --> 01:14:36,930
Hold him down.

529
01:15:11,507 --> 01:15:13,091
More dingo-dongos maybe.

530
01:15:17,721 --> 01:15:19,056
Lucky.

531
01:15:22,392 --> 01:15:24,603
I know what's coming.

532
01:15:25,646 --> 01:15:29,149
Called to find you. 
The serpents...

533
01:15:50,212 --> 01:15:51,463
spotlight!

534
01:16:18,574 --> 01:16:19,908
Like I said,

535
01:16:21,326 --> 01:16:23,829
it ain't me you 
gotta worry about.

536
01:16:28,333 --> 01:16:30,544
What is it? What's out there?

537
01:16:31,003 --> 01:16:32,254
I don't know.

538
01:16:33,338 --> 01:16:34,840
Fucked up or 
something out there.

539
01:16:35,465 --> 01:16:38,844
It ain't right. 
It's coming our way.

540
01:16:47,936 --> 01:16:51,189
Whatever they are, they 
ain't so hard to kill.

541
01:17:31,146 --> 01:17:33,565
What the fuck?

542
01:17:54,586 --> 01:17:55,796
Fuck!

543
01:18:10,185 --> 01:18:12,187
No more holes, please.

544
01:18:33,959 --> 01:18:37,045
What the fuck is happening? 
How fucked are we?

545
01:18:37,421 --> 01:18:39,923
Who knows how long 
it will rain?

546
01:18:41,425 --> 01:18:45,554
Or just how many of them 
are buried out there?

547
01:18:47,639 --> 01:18:51,727
He saw it. He saw it with those eyes 
of his and he didn't tell us what.

548
01:19:01,695 --> 01:19:04,823
One ship for you, one for me.

549
01:19:05,699 --> 01:19:08,785
I need to know that these 
nodes are retrievable.

550
01:19:10,454 --> 01:19:12,956
And I need to know 
we have a deal.

551
01:19:17,335 --> 01:19:18,962
We got a deal.

552
01:19:26,303 --> 01:19:28,555
The chains stay on.

553
01:19:41,777 --> 01:19:43,737
Why don't we sit this one out?

554
01:19:46,698 --> 01:19:47,949
Okay. Okay.

555
01:19:49,659 --> 01:19:51,369
Up, up, up...

556
01:19:54,623 --> 01:19:56,082
Good doggie.

557
01:20:20,899 --> 01:20:21,900
Oh!

558
01:20:22,943 --> 01:20:25,153
Holy shit.

559
01:21:17,789 --> 01:21:20,667
Where the hell did that... Jesus Christ!

560
01:21:21,876 --> 01:21:23,086
No, no, no!

561
01:21:25,797 --> 01:21:28,550
What the fuck is wrong with 
you, you crazy bastard?

562
01:21:28,592 --> 01:21:29,843
You could have killed me!

563
01:21:29,926 --> 01:21:31,678
Got it, didn't I?

564
01:21:39,811 --> 01:21:41,438
Vargas, get up.

565
01:21:42,230 --> 01:21:44,357
Vargas, get up. 
Come on, let's go.

566
01:21:44,691 --> 01:21:46,318
Vargas, come on, man. 
Walk it off.

567
01:21:46,401 --> 01:21:48,028
Let's go. It's 
just a little one.

568
01:21:48,320 --> 01:21:50,196
Small ones are the worst.

569
01:21:51,823 --> 01:21:53,992
They save the most venom.

570
01:22:14,387 --> 01:22:16,264
I forgot to mention,

571
01:22:17,766 --> 01:22:19,643
there's no weapons for you.

572
01:22:26,399 --> 01:22:28,401
You think you can ride 
one of these things?

573
01:22:28,943 --> 01:22:31,029
I'll ride it like I stole it.

574
01:22:45,585 --> 01:22:47,212
I'll take flank.

575
01:22:58,098 --> 01:23:00,350
If Riddick comes back 
here without us,

576
01:23:00,392 --> 01:23:03,520
you go ahead, you kill him 
on general principle.

577
01:23:03,728 --> 01:23:06,815
Is that before or after 
I'm supposed to fuck him?

578
01:25:41,511 --> 01:25:44,389
How bad you want 
those nodes, Johns?

579
01:26:20,174 --> 01:26:23,511
I don't suppose you took the 
time to do this for him, huh?

580
01:26:25,638 --> 01:26:28,391
This may come as a 
shock to you, Johns,

581
01:26:29,809 --> 01:26:31,811
but I didn't ghost your son.

582
01:26:33,897 --> 01:26:36,482
He seemed set on 
killing himself.

583
01:26:39,861 --> 01:26:41,738
What the fuck does that mean?

584
01:26:42,488 --> 01:26:43,948
Morphine.

585
01:26:45,491 --> 01:26:47,118
Your son liked his morphine.

586
01:26:48,411 --> 01:26:50,371
Liked it twice a day.

587
01:26:51,205 --> 01:26:53,708
Didn't know your 
son was a junkie?

588
01:26:57,212 --> 01:26:59,214
Johns was like most Mercs.

589
01:26:59,923 --> 01:27:03,259
They look all 
stand-up and do-right

590
01:27:03,927 --> 01:27:06,804
until you out them open and 
you find something missing.

591
01:27:07,764 --> 01:27:09,641
In his case, a spine.

592
01:27:11,517 --> 01:27:14,979
I don't have to listen to this 
shit! That's not the man I knew.

593
01:27:15,104 --> 01:27:17,482
Then you didn't know your son.

594
01:27:22,570 --> 01:27:24,656
He wanted to kill a kid.

595
01:27:26,282 --> 01:27:28,159
To save his own skin.

596
01:27:28,701 --> 01:27:30,828
I had a problem with that.

597
01:27:32,121 --> 01:27:34,123
You expect me to believe

598
01:27:34,624 --> 01:27:37,877
my son was gonna kill a 
child to save his own life?

599
01:27:40,088 --> 01:27:43,716
Morphine makes the 
brain soft. Heart weak.

600
01:27:47,470 --> 01:27:49,472
I don't fucking buy it!

601
01:27:49,889 --> 01:27:52,100
I just can't believe that 
my son's the bad guy

602
01:27:52,141 --> 01:27:55,269
in this fucking demented 
fairy tale of yours.

603
01:27:58,106 --> 01:28:00,066
No reason to lie now.

604
01:28:02,944 --> 01:28:04,153
Johns.

605
01:28:07,365 --> 01:28:08,866
Either one of us.

606
01:28:38,146 --> 01:28:40,648
Thanks for starting the killing 
spree for me, Riddick.

607
01:28:40,690 --> 01:28:42,567
But I'll take it from here.

608
01:29:35,203 --> 01:29:36,537
Jamoke.

609
01:29:41,501 --> 01:29:44,462
So that blade you buried 
was meant for me?

610
01:29:45,922 --> 01:29:48,424
Anyone who deserved 
it, really.

611
01:29:51,803 --> 01:29:53,179
We've got a problem, Riddick,

612
01:29:55,098 --> 01:29:57,725
because I've got 
two nodes here.

613
01:29:57,767 --> 01:29:59,644
We've got one hog.

614
01:29:59,769 --> 01:30:03,898
And I sure as shit am not 
riding bitch with you again.

615
01:30:06,150 --> 01:30:07,485
One hog?

616
01:30:08,945 --> 01:30:10,780
You sure about that, Johns?

617
01:30:16,661 --> 01:30:19,247
He pulled the goddamn 
turbine pin!

618
01:30:20,706 --> 01:30:22,792
You just figured that out?

619
01:30:23,334 --> 01:30:26,838
Diaz was gonna take the nodes 
for himself and ghost me.

620
01:30:27,296 --> 01:30:30,007
He was gonna leave 
you out here alone.

621
01:30:30,466 --> 01:30:31,968
So what now?

622
01:30:39,350 --> 01:30:41,811
Now we switch to 
our ground game.

623
01:30:43,312 --> 01:30:46,691
Let's see if that lack of 
spine runs in the family.

624
01:31:38,701 --> 01:31:39,952
Reload!

625
01:31:46,250 --> 01:31:47,960
Watch your head.

626
01:31:58,304 --> 01:31:59,430
Go!

627
01:34:02,678 --> 01:34:03,804
I got inbound.

628
01:34:19,111 --> 01:34:20,738
Take this!

629
01:34:21,030 --> 01:34:22,782
Is it just you?

630
01:34:23,657 --> 01:34:25,993
Just slam this thing in. 
See if it's still good.

631
01:34:29,372 --> 01:34:30,373
Boss...

632
01:34:30,456 --> 01:34:34,043
Just see if the fucking thing 
works! We need to get outta here.

633
01:38:38,329 --> 01:38:41,832
Extraction, 30 seconds or less. 
Let's go, let's go!

634
01:39:54,363 --> 01:39:56,365
<i>Lot of good 
men died here, Riddick.</i>

635
01:39:56,615 --> 01:40:00,577
Not sure how I'm supposed to 
overlook that. Next time.

636
01:40:00,911 --> 01:40:02,913
Yeah. Things would 
have been different

637
01:40:03,038 --> 01:40:05,416
if they weren't trying 
to put my head in a box.

638
01:40:08,085 --> 01:40:10,170
So where to now, Riddick?

639
01:40:10,796 --> 01:40:14,758
You know what? Fuck that. 
Don't tell me. I don't wanna know.

640
01:40:15,551 --> 01:40:17,553
<i>I'll tell you this, Johns.</i>

641
01:40:17,928 --> 01:40:21,181
<i>Sooner or later, we all 
have to head home.</i>

642
01:40:22,141 --> 01:40:24,393
<i>Tell Dahl to keep 
it warm for me.</i>

643
01:40:25,144 --> 01:40:26,645
And, Johns,

644
01:40:27,896 --> 01:40:30,023
you keep a strong spine.

645
01:41:17,362 --> 01:41:18,363
Vaako.

646
01:41:21,366 --> 01:41:23,827
- You are still alive. 
- Tell me where.

647
01:41:25,954 --> 01:41:27,831
He's no longer among us.

648
01:41:27,873 --> 01:41:30,876
Tell me, and I'll 
kill him first.

649
01:41:31,460 --> 01:41:32,711
You misunderstand.

650
01:41:33,253 --> 01:41:35,839
Vaako is a decent man who 
meant to honor his word.

651
01:41:36,799 --> 01:41:38,759
Even with you, strangely.

652
01:41:38,967 --> 01:41:40,677
I don't care about Furya.

653
01:41:40,719 --> 01:41:43,347
I don't care what the pact 
was between you and him.

654
01:41:43,388 --> 01:41:45,724
This faith cannot 
have a misbeliever

655
01:41:45,766 --> 01:41:47,267
or a kind heart leading it,

656
01:41:47,309 --> 01:41:50,395
and I have done what I have 
done to ensure...

657
01:42:00,322 --> 01:42:01,949
Too many words.

658
01:42:16,922 --> 01:42:19,299
Never lie to me, 
I'll never hurt you.

659
01:42:22,970 --> 01:42:24,429
One word answer.

660
01:42:26,807 --> 01:42:28,308
Is Vaako alive or dead?

661
01:42:33,814 --> 01:42:34,815
Both.

662
01:42:57,963 --> 01:42:59,715
<i>Transcendence.</i>

